<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I'm a 35 DE necro and would like to do this quest.<BR>
However there was a comment in a previous post about losing factions with The Dead when completing it. How bad exactly is this?<BR>
Another thing crossed my mind when I read the Albonez' post. Sounds pretty cool, but I guess You could decrease the danger of dying by using the clay balls once for the father in Felwithe and once for the mother in Erudin. Lina could be evaded (or killed) after getting the letter from her, she's weak. And you probably could get near her mother while invisible.<BR>
The hard part would be to find a safe place inside the palace for switching from invisible to elemental form (remember the guards are kos to elemental form). Would that work? Or are any other mobs surrounding the mother kos to elemental? Guards or other NPC's?<BR>
Would like to be enlightened in that matter,<BR>
Codlugarthia Muerte,<BR>
35th Necro of Rodcet Nife</font></td></tr></table>
